Time since level 1.
This is a continuation of the 'Backstory by each year' section for if you are starting after the first level. This section involves writing what your character has been doing since level 1, aka since their backstory.
To do this, you can decide at what age the character became level 1, and what age they are now. Example: Level 1 at age 20, level 10 at age 25. This example would put the character at a progression rate of 6 months to 1 level. For a human this is pretty normal, but for an elf you may space levels out over decades, longer for some other races.
Assuming level 1 at age 20, that means they came level 1 in 4705 AR. Now we expand out your 'backstory by each year' section but including 'level x' after the age of our character before the colon.
Example = 4705 AR, age 20, level 2: Killed my first human and drunk their blood, sanity is starting to leave me…

307 AG, Pharast 1st - After a few weeks of finishing his final preparations he leaves Lajok.
307 AG - For the rest of the year he just travelled, visiting multiple worlds. Like a scouting mission, just seeing what is to be seen and recording it for later. Learned some intricacies of a couple of the languages he studied back home.
308 AG - As his initial funds started to run out he started taking random jobs. As mundane as delivering packages to as extreme as providing recon/sniper support. This is where he first killed another sentient being.
         These odd jobs did sometimes include transport to other worlds. Eventually near the end of the year a job took him to Absalom Station where he ended up taking a courier job for AbadarCorp that kept him on station.
309 AG - Quickly started immersing himself in the culture and people of the Station. Found himself drawn to the energy of the nightlife; clubs, concerts, sex, drugs. Found a club that had an open night for people to just come together on stage and go wild. While still just a beginner he loved the raw, deep thrums of a bass guitar and the heavy beats from the drums that vibrated his body and let him feel the music in a new way than just being in the crowd.
         After one of those performances he met a guy who he hit it off with. A Skittermander by the name of Sparrkz. The very stereotype of his people. It was a whirlwind romance and they quickly did almost everything together when they had free time. Eventually, however, their dreams for their life started to cause problems so they mutually ended things. They did stay friends even with the issues they still enjoyed each other's company and frequently acted as wingmen for the other, to sometimes hilarious results.
310 AG - The first couple of months were fairly quiet and ordinary between work and clubbing. However on Pharast 7th he witnessed a drug deal gone wrong in an alley behind the club he had been at as he was leaving to head home. The dealer had beaten the victim badly and when they saw him they tried to attack him as well. Thanks to his training he was able to react quickly and shot the dealer dead.
         The aftermath resulted in an investigation and temporarily being unable to work for two weeks. During that time he learned that Sota, his home star, had mysteriously reignited. Once his suspension due to the investigation ended he started doing more extra jobs and clubbing less to save for a trip back home.

